my_module/
│
├── __init__.py                # Makes this folder a Python package
├── __manifest__.py            # Module description, dependencies, metadata
│
├── controllers/               # HTTP controllers (website, REST APIs, etc.)
│   └── __init__.py
│   └── my_controller.py
│
├── models/                    # Business logic & ORM models
│   └── __init__.py
│   └── my_model.py
│
├── views/                     # XML views (forms, trees, kanban, etc.)
│   └── my_model_views.xml
│   └── templates.xml
│
├── data/                      # Initial data files (XML/CSV)
│   └── my_data.xml
│
├── security/                  # Access control & security rules
│   └── ir.model.access.csv
│   └── security.xml
│
├── report/                    # QWeb or PDF reports
│   └── report.xml
│   └── report_template.xml
│
├── wizards/                   # Transient models (popup wizards)
│   └── wizard_model.py
│   └── wizard_views.xml
│
├── static/                    # Static files (JS, CSS, images)
│   ├── description/           # Module icon, README images
│   ├── img/                   # Custom images
│   ├── src/                   # Web assets (JS/CSS)
│   │   ├── js/
│   │   ├── scss/
│   │   └── xml/               # QWeb templates
│
├── demo/                      # Demo data (loaded in demo mode)
│   └── demo_data.xml
│
└── tests/                     # Python test cases
    └── test_my_module.py



=========================================================================================
Key Files

__manifest__.py → Defines module name, version, dependencies, category, installable status, etc.
__init__.py → Imports Python files so Odoo can load them.
ir.model.access.csv → Controls model access per user groups.
views/*.xml → Contains form/tree/kanban views, menus, and actions.
static/src/ → Frontend assets for Odoo’s web client.
wizards/ → For transient models that only live in memory during an action.